1
00:02:02,862 --> 00:02:05,365
[CLONE GUARD A] Attack from
Second Baleras complete.

2
00:02:05,448 --> 00:02:07,200
[MORI]
What have you done?

3
00:02:07,283 --> 00:02:09,661
[DESLER]
Oh, just a little idea of mine.

4
00:02:09,744 --> 00:02:12,747
I've tried using Wave
Motion Energy as a weapon.

5
00:02:12,831 --> 00:02:14,207
A Wave Motion Gun?

6
00:02:14,290 --> 00:02:16,292
[CLONE GUARD A] The <i>Yamato</i>
appears to be destroyed.

7
00:02:16,376 --> 00:02:17,794
After a long journey,

8
00:02:17,877 --> 00:02:20,338
they were killed just
before reaching their goal.

9
00:02:20,422 --> 00:02:23,717
There's beauty in its perfectly
tragic end, don't you think?

10
00:02:25,885 --> 00:02:30,015
I wonder what the Teron
captain was like.

11
00:02:30,098 --> 00:02:31,599
I'd love to have met the man,

12
00:02:31,683 --> 00:02:35,770
to thank him for giving me
such a rousing challenge.

13
00:02:35,854 --> 00:02:39,274
Our dear Princess Yurisha
seems to be feeling unwell.

14
00:02:39,357 --> 00:02:41,401
Perhaps she needs fresh air.

15
00:02:41,484 --> 00:02:43,445
Let's go.

16
00:02:45,697 --> 00:02:47,490
[CLONE GUARD B] Something on
radar near point of impact.

17
00:02:47,574 --> 00:02:49,451
It's the <i>Yamato</i> !

18
00:02:49,534 --> 00:02:51,244
[NANBU]
AA guns badly damaged!

19
00:02:51,327 --> 00:02:52,662
[OTA]
Sensors malfunctioning!

20
00:02:52,746 --> 00:02:54,706
[MISAKI]
The planet's collapsing!

21
00:02:54,789 --> 00:02:56,374
Epidra is lost.

22
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:59,336
A weapon that can destroy
planets with one shot?

23
00:02:59,419 --> 00:03:02,005
A Wave Motion Gun.

24
00:03:02,088 --> 00:03:04,758
Picking up fluctuations in
the gravitational gradient.

25
00:03:04,841 --> 00:03:09,179
This waveform is consistent
with a wave motion attack.

26
00:03:09,262 --> 00:03:10,764
We are not retreating.

27
00:03:10,847 --> 00:03:14,142
We'll continue
to the inner system.

28
00:03:14,225 --> 00:03:16,227
Any wave motion weapon
should have difficulty

29
00:03:16,311 --> 00:03:18,730
targeting a ship moving
at sub-light-speed.

30
00:03:18,813 --> 00:03:20,523
And without moving
deep into their range,

31
00:03:20,607 --> 00:03:22,650
we have no way to win.

32
00:03:22,734 --> 00:03:26,029
Full speed ahead.
New target, Gamilas!

33
00:03:29,783 --> 00:03:32,660
[CLONE GUARD B] <i>Yamato</i> heading
toward us at sub-light-speed!

34
00:03:32,744 --> 00:03:34,204
[DESLER]
Interesting.

35
00:03:34,287 --> 00:03:36,956
[CLONE GUARD C] Minister Talan
hailing from Second Baleras.

36
00:03:40,877 --> 00:03:44,047
My lord, as anticipated, firing
at maximum available power

37
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:45,924
has damaged the system.

38
00:03:46,007 --> 00:03:48,051
Complete the repairs
as soon as you can.

39
00:03:48,134 --> 00:03:49,594
They're at sub-light-speed.

40
00:03:49,678 --> 00:03:52,263
Targeting with the Desler Cannon
will be close to impossible!

41
00:03:52,347 --> 00:03:53,515
It won't work!

42
00:03:53,598 --> 00:03:56,101
Patience, Talan, they'll
be slowing down soon.

43
00:03:56,184 --> 00:03:57,644
[CLONE GUARD C]
My lord.

44
00:03:57,727 --> 00:04:01,064
Her Royal Highness Queen
Starsha is on the hotline.

45
00:04:01,147 --> 00:04:03,650
She wants to speak
to you directly.

46
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:07,237
[STARSHA] Lord Desler, how
could you even consider this?

47
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:09,781
Weaponizing Wave Motion
Energy is madness.

48
00:04:09,864 --> 00:04:12,534
And in our own system no less!

49
00:04:12,617 --> 00:04:15,662
--Are you here to complain?
--I am.

50
00:04:15,745 --> 00:04:17,706
You're always complaining.

51
00:04:17,789 --> 00:04:19,374
Have you noticed
that's the only reason

52
00:04:19,457 --> 00:04:22,043
you ever grace me with
your presence anymore?

53
00:04:22,127 --> 00:04:23,586
Well if you're so incensed,

54
00:04:23,670 --> 00:04:26,548
then why don't you go
complain to the Terons?

55
00:04:26,631 --> 00:04:28,174
And what does that mean?

56
00:04:28,258 --> 00:04:29,759
[DESLER]
That ship you brought here

57
00:04:29,843 --> 00:04:31,636
also weaponizes
Wave Motion Energy.

58
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,972
They've used it for some time.

59
00:04:34,055 --> 00:04:35,724
That can't be.

60
00:04:35,807 --> 00:04:38,226
While you're here,
I assume you noticed

61
00:04:38,309 --> 00:04:41,813
your little sister is with us.
She's doing quite well.

62
00:04:41,896 --> 00:04:43,356
[STARSHA gasps]

63
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,942
I've ordered that she be
kept here, safe and secure.

64
00:04:46,026 --> 00:04:49,404
How far are you going to
take this? To what end?

65
00:04:49,487 --> 00:04:51,698
[DESLER]
But I'm doing it all for you.

66
00:04:51,781 --> 00:04:53,241
Stop it.

67
00:04:53,324 --> 00:04:54,784
[DESLER]
Starsha.

68
00:04:54,868 --> 00:04:56,870
Please, don't!

69
00:05:01,124 --> 00:05:04,085
I see. That's too bad.

70
00:05:06,755 --> 00:05:10,216
[STARSHA]
Please, Abelt. Don't do this.

71
00:05:14,929 --> 00:05:17,140
[MISAKI] Three ships at
ten o'clock. Carriers!

72
00:05:17,223 --> 00:05:18,933
[SANADA]
Deploy Wave Motion Shields.

73
00:05:19,017 --> 00:05:20,602
[OKITA]
No.

74
00:05:20,685 --> 00:05:22,228
Not yet.

75
00:05:22,312 --> 00:05:23,563
Yes, sir.

76
00:05:23,646 --> 00:05:26,691
Slow down to half speed.
Then send out the Falcons!

77
00:05:43,917 --> 00:05:46,586
[KILLMENHEIM CM A] Front carrier
fleet will soon encounter enemy.

78
00:05:46,670 --> 00:05:48,213
Have them attack.

79
00:05:48,296 --> 00:05:50,423
Launch the Melancas now.

80
00:05:55,136 --> 00:05:58,181
[KATO] Don't let 'em near the
<i>Yamato</i> . Shoot 'em down!

81
00:06:03,478 --> 00:06:05,021
Turn us hard to starboard.

82
00:06:05,105 --> 00:06:07,857
I want the bow pointing
straight at Gamilas!

83
00:06:52,736 --> 00:06:54,738
[CLONE GUARD D] Major damage
to forward carrier fleet.

84
00:06:54,821 --> 00:06:56,531
[CLONE GUARD B]
The <i>Yamato</i> is descending.

85
00:06:56,614 --> 00:06:59,743
Ultimately, our goal is
protecting the new capital.

86
00:06:59,826 --> 00:07:02,620
But I still want to give
our leader a good show.

87
00:07:18,219 --> 00:07:20,555
[MELDA] That's Baleras ahead,
the Imperial capital.

88
00:07:20,638 --> 00:07:23,433
Cross this ravine and you'll
have a clear path to the palace.

89
00:07:23,516 --> 00:07:25,810
Mm. That sounds good to me.

90
00:07:25,894 --> 00:07:29,147
Head for the palace. We'll
strike right at their heart.

91
00:07:37,822 --> 00:07:40,408
[HYSS] We've allowed the
enemy in to our home world?

92
00:07:40,492 --> 00:07:42,369
What is the Imperial
Guard doing?

93
00:07:42,452 --> 00:07:45,163
Gimleh. I told you
he was useless.

94
00:07:46,164 --> 00:07:51,169
♪

95
00:08:27,372 --> 00:08:29,708
Deploy Wave Motion Shields.

96
00:08:46,307 --> 00:08:48,309
[OKITA]
We're going to ram the palace.

97
00:08:55,692 --> 00:08:58,236
All crew, brace for impact!

98
00:09:01,281 --> 00:09:02,699
[MORI gasps]

99
00:09:17,839 --> 00:09:19,007
[OKITA groans]

100
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:20,592
Captain. Are you okay?

101
00:09:20,675 --> 00:09:22,677
I want all crew
armed with weapons.

102
00:09:22,761 --> 00:09:26,264
Kodai, assemble a strike
team with you in command.

103
00:09:29,517 --> 00:09:31,603
We'd better get out of here.

104
00:09:34,773 --> 00:09:36,524
Uh!

105
00:09:36,608 --> 00:09:39,527
That's exactly what
I thought you'd say.

106
00:09:39,611 --> 00:09:40,779
[OPERATOR D]
Damage report, now!

107
00:09:40,862 --> 00:09:42,280
[OPERATOR C] The palace
wall has been breached!

108
00:09:42,364 --> 00:09:43,656
[HYSS]
Impossible.

109
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:44,991
[CELESTRA]
Is our leader safe?

110
00:09:45,075 --> 00:09:46,826
Send in soldiers
to find him, now!

111
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:48,370
Let's not panic.

112
00:09:48,453 --> 00:09:50,705
[PA VOICE A] Initiating
<i>Deusura</i> decoupling sequence.

113
00:09:50,789 --> 00:09:52,457
{\an8}The <i>Deusura</i> ?

114
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:53,875
{\an8}[CELESTRA]
Out of the way!

115
00:09:53,958 --> 00:10:02,133
{\an8}[PA VOICE A speaking Gamilan]

116
00:10:12,352 --> 00:10:15,021
What? We're accelerating.

117
00:10:17,315 --> 00:10:19,526
[MISAKI] Something's
launched from the palace!

118
00:10:21,528 --> 00:10:23,863
I can tell.

119
00:10:23,947 --> 00:10:26,324
Yuki is onboard.

120
00:10:29,953 --> 00:10:33,665
My lord, you left me behind?

121
00:10:33,748 --> 00:10:37,919
But why? Why would you leave
me?!

122
00:10:39,337 --> 00:10:41,423
My lord. We should
acquire full control

123
00:10:41,506 --> 00:10:43,842
of Second Baleras momentarily.

124
00:10:43,925 --> 00:10:45,885
Everything is going as planned.

125
00:10:45,969 --> 00:10:47,345
Yes, sir.

126
00:10:47,429 --> 00:10:49,681
Then it is time to
begin the operation!

127
00:10:49,764 --> 00:10:51,349
Zar Belk.

128
00:10:54,310 --> 00:10:55,812
[BALERAS II OFFICER A]
Minister Talan,

129
00:10:55,895 --> 00:10:59,149
our central control system is
being taken over from outside!

130
00:10:59,232 --> 00:11:00,817
[VELTE]
Find the origin.

131
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:04,112
What the--? It's coming
from the <i>Deusura</i> !

132
00:11:04,195 --> 00:11:06,239
--Lord Desler?
--Ah! Minister, sir!

133
00:11:06,322 --> 00:11:09,159
Industrial Sector 633
is decoupling!

134
00:11:09,242 --> 00:11:11,244
Uh. That can't be.

135
00:11:32,682 --> 00:11:35,268
[YURISHA]
Forget this palace.

136
00:11:35,352 --> 00:11:38,438
Go after that vessel
and rescue Yuki!

137
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,941
Strike team is ready to go!

138
00:11:42,025 --> 00:11:43,360
Kodai!

139
00:11:43,443 --> 00:11:44,986
[MISAKI]
I've found something on radar!

140
00:11:45,070 --> 00:11:46,988
Magnify it!

141
00:11:47,072 --> 00:11:49,449
[MISAKI] It's a massive
object falling from orbit!

142
00:11:49,532 --> 00:11:51,951
[ANALYZER] Estimated mass:
60 million tons.

143
00:11:52,035 --> 00:11:54,454
Descending from
Lagrange point L-One.

144
00:11:54,537 --> 00:11:56,956
Estimated impact
point is the palace.

145
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,958
In other words: Here.

146
00:12:00,627 --> 00:12:02,253
[OPERATOR C]
It's continuing to drop.

147
00:12:02,337 --> 00:12:03,380
[OPERATOR D]
The decoupling command

148
00:12:03,463 --> 00:12:05,048
came from Lord Desler himself.

149
00:12:05,131 --> 00:12:06,424
From Lord Desler?

150
00:12:06,508 --> 00:12:08,968
[OPERATOR B] Impact at
approximately 2,400 gek.

151
00:12:09,052 --> 00:12:11,304
But this doesn't make any sense.

152
00:12:12,555 --> 00:12:16,810
Everyone, evacuate! Declare
an emergency in the capital!

153
00:12:16,893 --> 00:12:18,228
[PA VOICE A]
This is not a drill.

154
00:12:18,311 --> 00:12:21,189
All personnel must evacuate
palace immediately.

155
00:12:21,272 --> 00:12:25,485
Repeat: all personnel must
evacuate palace immediately.

156
00:12:25,568 --> 00:12:28,071
We can't stay here, sir!

157
00:12:28,154 --> 00:12:31,783
How could he? How could
our leader do this?

158
00:12:31,866 --> 00:12:34,160
Desler!

159
00:12:37,205 --> 00:12:39,082
[OPERATOR E]
Guidance beacon, locked.

160
00:13:01,271 --> 00:13:02,397
[OPERATOR F]
Docking complete.

161
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,649
Connected to Desler
Cannon circuit.

162
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:06,943
[LECTER]
Minister Talan is here.

163
00:13:07,027 --> 00:13:09,904
My lord, tell me why
you're doing this, please.

164
00:13:09,988 --> 00:13:14,034
Why are you dropping Sector
633 on Baleras? Why?

165
00:13:14,117 --> 00:13:15,910
[DESLER]
It's a rite of passage, Talan.

166
00:13:15,994 --> 00:13:17,537
A rite of passage?

167
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:20,331
[DESLER] Baleras and the <i>Yamato</i>
will be annihilated together.

168
00:13:20,415 --> 00:13:23,376
And from the smoldering ashes
of this noble sacrifice.

169
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:26,212
A more perfect
Gamilas will be born.

170
00:13:27,756 --> 00:13:29,466
When this operation is done,

171
00:13:29,549 --> 00:13:32,886
Second Baleras will
descend to Iscandar.

172
00:13:32,969 --> 00:13:35,221
As of this moment
by imperial decree,

173
00:13:35,305 --> 00:13:37,015
this mobile
city fortress,

174
00:13:37,098 --> 00:13:39,517
this grand achievement we
have built in the heavens,

175
00:13:39,601 --> 00:13:41,644
will be the new
capital of Gamilas.

176
00:13:41,728 --> 00:13:45,690
A new center! A new Baleras!

177
00:13:45,774 --> 00:13:47,233
Splendid, my lord.

178
00:13:47,317 --> 00:13:49,319
[DESLER] This Second Baleras
shall be the ultimate bridge,

179
00:13:49,402 --> 00:13:53,406
uniting Gamilas and Iscandar
for our glorious future!

180
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:56,576
[ANALYZER] Estimated impact
on palace: 20 minutes.

181
00:13:56,659 --> 00:13:59,829
Prepare to fire the
Wave Motion Gun.

182
00:13:59,913 --> 00:14:00,997
Okita.

183
00:14:01,081 --> 00:14:02,165
It's the only hope we have

184
00:14:02,248 --> 00:14:04,209
for destroying a
structure that massive.

185
00:14:04,292 --> 00:14:07,128
With the gun,
we can save this city.

186
00:14:07,212 --> 00:14:12,967
Proving it with actions,
not with your words. Mm.

187
00:14:14,678 --> 00:14:17,722
This is a moment when
we all must do our best.

188
00:14:17,806 --> 00:14:19,724
As our hearts compel us.

189
00:14:19,808 --> 00:14:22,102
What we alone can achieve.

190
00:14:22,185 --> 00:14:25,438
--I'm going after Yuki!
--[KODAI] No.

191
00:14:25,522 --> 00:14:28,942
Sorry. But it should be me.

192
00:14:30,318 --> 00:14:31,861
Captain, please, sir.

193
00:14:31,945 --> 00:14:34,239
Requesting use of a Zero.

194
00:14:34,322 --> 00:14:37,075
Kodai. I hereby
relieve you of your duties

195
00:14:37,158 --> 00:14:40,036
as <i>Yamato</i> 's Chief of Tactical.

196
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:43,039
As of now, I'm giving
you another mission.

197
00:14:43,123 --> 00:14:46,084
Rescue Lieutenant Mori,
whatever it takes.

198
00:14:46,167 --> 00:14:47,794
Yes, sir!

199
00:14:51,131 --> 00:14:54,342
[OKITA] You may take one
more person to assist.

200
00:14:54,426 --> 00:14:55,969
Thanks, Captain.

201
00:14:57,303 --> 00:14:58,471
[KODAI gasps]

202
00:14:58,555 --> 00:15:01,766
Yes, Captain. I promise
I won't let you down.

203
00:15:04,936 --> 00:15:10,400
I've got this, sir. Just
please. Bring her back.

204
00:15:34,007 --> 00:15:35,091
Melda.

205
00:15:35,175 --> 00:15:37,385
[MELDA] Just protecting
Princess Yurisha.

206
00:15:53,485 --> 00:15:55,362
You leave them to me, Kodai.

207
00:15:55,445 --> 00:15:57,530
[MELDA]
She means to us.

208
00:15:57,614 --> 00:15:59,074
Everyone.

209
00:15:59,157 --> 00:16:01,993
We're doing our best,
what we alone can achieve.

210
00:16:02,077 --> 00:16:03,286
Ready?

211
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:05,789
Yeah. Yeah!

212
00:16:05,872 --> 00:16:07,791
Take care of Her Grace.

213
00:16:12,879 --> 00:16:15,465
Go, Kodai. Good luck.

214
00:16:16,549 --> 00:16:17,842
[PA VOICE B]
After linking with core ship,

215
00:16:17,926 --> 00:16:19,803
Company Six is to
load <i>Deusura II</i>

216
00:16:19,886 --> 00:16:21,680
and make primed for launch.

217
00:16:21,763 --> 00:16:23,765
[GAMILAN TECH A]
Get that resupply ready!

218
00:16:26,184 --> 00:16:28,561
[MORI]
Looks like the control room.

219
00:16:28,645 --> 00:16:31,272
[ORTSCHETT]
Aren't we trying to escape?

220
00:16:31,356 --> 00:16:32,941
[MORI] This craft has
a Wave Motion Gun,

221
00:16:33,024 --> 00:16:36,277
and if they use it, the <i>Yamato</i>
will never reach Iscandar.

222
00:16:36,361 --> 00:16:39,447
What are you trying to do?

223
00:16:39,531 --> 00:16:41,700
I'm gonna try to destroy it.

224
00:16:43,743 --> 00:16:45,286
Sealing emergency vents.

225
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:46,913
[NANBU]
Releasing safety lock.

226
00:16:46,996 --> 00:16:48,790
[KITANO]
Target in range.

227
00:16:48,873 --> 00:16:51,960
[SHIMA] Adjusting angle
of incline. Raising bow.

228
00:16:53,962 --> 00:16:56,006
Stabilize the hull.

229
00:16:59,175 --> 00:17:01,177
[PA VOICE A]
All citizens must evacuate.

230
00:17:01,261 --> 00:17:05,015
Impact is imminent.
Proceed to nearest transport.

231
00:17:05,098 --> 00:17:07,600
[TOKUGAWA] Tachyon particle
pressure rising in chamber.

232
00:17:07,684 --> 00:17:10,103
Energy charge 120%.

233
00:17:10,186 --> 00:17:13,606
Anti-shock and
anti-flare defenses.

234
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:18,194
[NANBU]
Four. Three. Two. One.

235
00:17:18,278 --> 00:17:19,738
Fire!

236
00:17:40,759 --> 00:17:43,970
The <i>Yamato</i> . They saved us all.

237
00:17:49,934 --> 00:17:51,478
<i>Yamato</i> ?

238
00:17:52,729 --> 00:17:54,773
[OKITA groaning]

239
00:17:54,856 --> 00:17:56,316
[thud]

240
00:17:56,399 --> 00:17:58,026
[SANADA]
Captain!

241
00:17:58,651 --> 00:18:00,362
[OPERATOR D] Six-Three-Three
engaged in route.

242
00:18:00,445 --> 00:18:01,905
[LECTER]
Very well.

243
00:18:01,988 --> 00:18:05,116
My lord, Desler Cannon is
back online and ready to fire.

244
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:06,451
[VELTE gasps]

245
00:18:06,534 --> 00:18:08,370
[DESLER]
Hm.

246
00:18:08,453 --> 00:18:10,080
[ORTSCHETT]
It's preparing to fire!

247
00:18:10,163 --> 00:18:11,539
[MORI]
Don't worry.

248
00:18:11,623 --> 00:18:12,874
[PA VOICE A]
Firing sequence...

249
00:18:12,957 --> 00:18:14,834
[MORI]
It's done.

250
00:18:14,918 --> 00:18:16,670
[PA VOICE A] ...prepare
for Wave Motion sequence.

251
00:18:16,753 --> 00:18:19,673
This will destabilize
the Wave Motion Core.

252
00:18:21,966 --> 00:18:23,677
Yuki.

253
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:26,262
Thanks for all your
help. Now go.

254
00:18:26,346 --> 00:18:28,640
You don't need to stick
around for the rest.

255
00:18:28,723 --> 00:18:29,849
There's still time--

256
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:33,019
Why are you willing to
make this sacrifice?

257
00:18:33,103 --> 00:18:34,979
Because it's finally clear.

258
00:18:35,063 --> 00:18:36,439
I understand it now.

259
00:18:36,523 --> 00:18:39,275
I'm doing what my
heart tells me to do.

260
00:18:39,359 --> 00:18:40,944
What I want most of all.

261
00:18:41,027 --> 00:18:43,113
--We do this...
--I do this...

262
00:18:43,196 --> 00:18:45,115
To keep you safe!

263
00:18:46,866 --> 00:18:48,368
Let's go, Zero!

264
00:18:48,451 --> 00:18:51,746
[YURISHA]
Ever faster! Ever higher!

265
00:18:52,288 --> 00:18:53,498
[PA VOICE A]
Begin routing all...

266
00:18:53,581 --> 00:18:55,583
No.

267
00:18:55,667 --> 00:18:57,585
Why, Norran?

268
00:18:57,669 --> 00:18:59,879
I thought that would be obvious.

269
00:19:00,964 --> 00:19:04,259
This is my chance to show
what I'm made of, too.

270
00:19:04,342 --> 00:19:08,054
If my lord learns I saved this
secret weapon from sabotage,

271
00:19:08,138 --> 00:19:10,724
he might even make me
a first-class Gamilan.

272
00:19:10,807 --> 00:19:12,767
You're not thinking! Ugh!

273
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:14,686
[ORTSCHETT]
Oh, trust me, I am!

274
00:19:14,769 --> 00:19:17,063
I've never been more certain.

275
00:19:17,147 --> 00:19:20,525
And that's why this
is our goodbye.

276
00:19:20,608 --> 00:19:22,819
[MORI yells]

277
00:19:22,902 --> 00:19:25,363
No, wait! Norran!

278
00:19:25,447 --> 00:19:27,615
You take care.

279
00:19:27,699 --> 00:19:29,909
[MORI]
Norran!

280
00:19:32,287 --> 00:19:34,122
[ORTSCHETT]
Farewell.

281
00:19:48,470 --> 00:19:50,180
[LECTER]
Firing hammer system activated.

282
00:19:50,263 --> 00:19:51,639
[DESLER]
Focus on the <i>Yamato</i> .

283
00:19:51,723 --> 00:19:54,642
Channel all the energy we have.

284
00:19:54,726 --> 00:19:56,936
My lord, you can't do this!

285
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:59,064
You're about to fire
on your own people!

286
00:19:59,147 --> 00:20:01,316
Think of how many will die!

287
00:20:01,399 --> 00:20:04,903
[PA VOICE A] Desler Cannon final
firing sequence set to begin.

288
00:20:04,986 --> 00:20:09,908
[DESLER] That's why it must be
my hand that pulls the trigger.

289
00:20:09,991 --> 00:20:11,951
I must be the one
who commits the sin

290
00:20:12,035 --> 00:20:15,914
of sacrificing so many noble
lives for the future of Gamilas.

291
00:20:15,997 --> 00:20:18,625
It will haunt me. But for
the sake of the empire,

292
00:20:18,708 --> 00:20:21,878
I will bear this
burden on my soul.

293
00:20:26,341 --> 00:20:27,217
What the--?

294
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,885
[PA VOICE A]
Warning. Warning.

295
00:20:28,968 --> 00:20:31,805
Wave Motion Core failing.
Safety limits exceeded.

296
00:20:31,888 --> 00:20:34,432
Explosive compression immin...

297
00:20:34,557 --> 00:20:38,478
[ORTSCHETT] It's funny.
I was willing to go this far.

298
00:20:38,561 --> 00:20:41,439
But never learned her real name.

299
00:20:41,523 --> 00:20:42,649
[OPERATOR 23D]
The core's about to blow!

300
00:20:42,732 --> 00:20:44,526
--Jump now!
--Yes, sir!

301
00:20:55,870 --> 00:20:58,873
No. Goodbye, Norran.

302
00:20:58,957 --> 00:21:01,126
You're a terrible liar.

303
00:21:03,378 --> 00:21:04,546
[KILLMENHEIM CM A]
The other ships are gone!

304
00:21:04,629 --> 00:21:06,172
Explosion incoming!

305
00:21:06,256 --> 00:21:08,008
[GAMILAN OFFICER A]
Evasive action! Get away!

306
00:21:08,091 --> 00:21:09,217
[KILLMENHEIM CM A]
There's no time!

307
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:12,137
My, what a shame.
So this is how it ends.

308
00:21:17,434 --> 00:21:21,438
[MISAKI] Enemy station appears
to be collapsing, sir.

309
00:21:21,521 --> 00:21:23,773
What in the world
happened out there?

310
00:21:31,114 --> 00:21:33,700
In the end, I lost her.

311
00:21:41,207 --> 00:21:43,168
[gasps]

312
00:21:45,128 --> 00:21:50,133
♪

313
00:22:10,779 --> 00:22:12,947
[MORI]
I'm not dreaming, am I?

314
00:22:13,031 --> 00:22:15,992
No. This is real.

